General Assembly Proposed Bill No. 5116
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 687
Referred to Committee on FINANCE, REVENUE AND
BONDING
Introduced by:
REP. GODFREY, 110th Dist.
AN ACT REDUCING THE RATE OF THE SALES AND USE TAXES.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 That chapter 219 of the general statutes be amended to reduce the rate
2 of the sales and use taxes to six per cent.
Statement of Purpose:
To reduce the rate of the sales and use taxes to six per cent.
